 but no chart-related files match: emits reason, SKIP\n- `CHANGED_FILES` filtering: only `.yaml`/`.yml`/`.tpl` files are considered chart-related\n- Chart root deduplication: multiple changed files in same chart produce single invocation\n- `--help`/`help`/`-h`: handled before `need helm` so it works without helm installed\n- Unknown commands: prints usage and exits 2\n- `RUN_LINT=0` / `RUN_TEMPLATE=0` in `all` mode: skips respective steps\n- `FAIL_FAST`: uses `should_continue()` from shared lib\n- Multiple charts: per-chart sequential iteration with indexed log files\n- Subchart exclusion: `find` excludes `*/charts/*` to avoid processing vendored subcharts\n\n## Tests written/run\n- `tests/helm-agent/clean/` — valid chart passes with exit 0\n- `tests/helm-agent/issues/` — chart with required field error fails with exit 1\n- `tests/helm-agent/no-chart/` — empty dir produces SKIP with exit 0\n- All 3 scenarios correctly SKIP when `helm` is not installed (REQUIRED_TOOLS gating)\n- `shellcheck --severity=warning` passes on helm-agent.sh\n- Full suite: all 21 scenarios pass (including all existing agents), 0 failures\n\n## Known limitations\n- `CHANGED_FILES` splits on whitespace; paths with spaces are not supported (matches convention used by all other agents)\n- Scenario tests require `helm` to be installed to run the actual lint/template checks; they SKIP gracefully when missing\n- Test runner does not support EXTRA_ENV, so CHANGED_FILES scoping cannot be exercised in scenario tests\n\n## Feedback Closure Matrix\nNo prior review issues exist for this spec (first implementation).\n\n## Exploration notes\nUpdated `.ralph/exploration.md`: changed helm-agent from \"(to be added)\" to actual file path and description; updated tests/helm-agent description to reflect actual scenarios.\n\n## Lessons Applied This Phase\n- help-before-need: Parsed help flags before `need helm` so `--help` works without helm installed (pattern from bash-agent, go-agent, gha-agent)\n- Followed existing agent patterns (gha-agent) for file discovery, structured output, and scenario fixture format\n- Fixed shellcheck SC2221/SC2222 warning: `*.yaml` already covers `Chart.yaml` and `values.yaml` in case patterns\n\n## Suggestions for the REVIEW agent\n- Verify `--help` works without helm installed\n- The issues fixture uses `required \"requiredField must be set\"` on a missing value which should fail deterministically\n- Verify SKIP behavior when no `Chart.yaml` exists (no-chart scenario)\n- `CHANGED_FILES` scoping correctly filters `.yaml`/`.yml`/`.tpl` and finds parent Chart.yaml\n- Chart root deduplication via `seen` variable prevents duplicate runs\n- Subchart directories (`*/charts/*`) are excluded from recursive discovery\n","file_path":"/Users/chrisraethke/projects/x-agent/.ralph/work-summary.txt"}}
