10. What: Implement command routing and fail-fast behavior.
Why: FR-5 requires both command support and runtime control by `--fail-fast`.
How: Support `validate` and `all`; parse `--fail-fast` and in `all` path use `should_continue` with `RUN_VALIDATE` gate.
Edge Cases: explicit `all` with `RUN_VALIDATE=0`, unknown command.
Tests: `validate` command should run direct; `all` should no-op when `RUN_VALIDATE=0`.
Risks: `overall_ok` not initialized before use.

11. What: Add `skills/kube-agent/SKILL.md` metadata.
Why: Agent invocation depends on metadata and allowed-tools completeness.
How: Mirror existing SKILL format for agents, include triggers and `allowed-tools`: `RUN_*`, `MAX_LINES`, `KEEP_DIR`, `FAIL_FAST`, `CHANGED_FILES`, `KUBE_SCHEMAS_DIR`, `TMPDIR_ROOT`.
Edge Cases: missing `TMPDIR_ROOT` entry if project policy requires it.
Tests: static review before implementation handoff.
Risks: install/invocation mismatch due missing patterns.

12. What: Create clean fixture and invalid fixture under `tests/kube-agent`.
Why: baseline pass/fail paths are required by acceptance.
How: add `clean/deployment.yaml`, `clean/scenario.env`, `issues/bad-deployment.yaml`, `issues/scenario.env` matching spec payloads and `REQUIRED_TOOLS="kubeconform"`.
Edge Cases: kubeconform absent -> fixture skipped by harness.
